Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.74,0:00:01.74,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.74,0:00:03.48,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,It was your doppelganger?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.69,0:00:04.64,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.64,0:00:08.73,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,So you didn't go to the concert hall that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.73,0:00:11.54,DCMain,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,N-No. Did we really look that similar?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.54,0:00:12.24,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.69,0:00:17.83,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,I was completed fooled when she \Nstopped me at the entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.12,0:00:20.37,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder who she was.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.80,0:00:22.76,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it was Kaito Kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.76,0:00:24.82,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,He must've come to steal my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.82,0:00:26.08,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.27,0:00:28.59,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It was Vermouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.27,0:00:32.46,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But if she bothered to investigate,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.46,0:00:35.79,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,the Black Organization must be interested
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.79,0:00:38.30,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,in the "ASACA RUM" \Ncipher left by Haneda Koji
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.05,0:00:42.16,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,seventeen years ago, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.88,0:00:45.88,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what she was after, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.88,0:00:47.69,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's kind of creepy.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.46,0:00:52.32,DCMain,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of creepy, when I went out \Nshopping for ingredients earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.54,0:00:55.82,DCMain,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,I saw a strange duo going \Nup to the detective agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.52,0:00:57.82,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A strange duo?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.22,0:01:00.86,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Were they dressed in black?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.86,0:01:03.88,DCMain,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,What? They were dressed \Nlike a normal couple.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.88,0:01:08.25,DCMain,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,The boyfriend's skin was dark \Nlike Amuro-san's though.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.43,0:01:09.63,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Dark?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.63,0:01:12.34,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Was it Makoto-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.34,0:01:14.51,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,What's he doing with another woman?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.95,0:01:19.57,DCMain,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,I-I wouldn't know, but they were \Ntalking about something strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.57,0:01:22.26,DCMain,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,Something about cleaning rags.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.80,0:01:25.06,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,R-Rags?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.81,0:01:28.95,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Curtains rise as the headliner appears!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.95,0:01:31.40,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He beautifully dances his \Nmystery-solving steps!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.40,0:01:33.52,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Rags dance in a terrifying case.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.52,0:01:35.42,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The forest where the nue's cry can \Nbe heard is a horrifying place.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.74,0:01:37.24,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.24,0:01:39.25,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.25,0:01:42.08,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.97,0:03:27.97,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(398,1)}Conan and Heiji's Nue Legend \N(Roar Arc)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.54,0:03:26.66,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"Conan and Heiji's Nue Legend, Roar Arc!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.97,0:03:31.73,DCNote,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Mori Detective Agency
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.10,0:03:34.15,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Not cleaning rags, rags to riches.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.15,0:03:35.40,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.40,0:03:37.74,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Rags to riches, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.74,0:03:39.61,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it was him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.99,0:03:43.39,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,The mayor of Yadori Village sent \NHeiji a letter asking him to help
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.39,0:03:45.96,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,unearth Tokugawa's buried treasure,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.96,0:03:48.72,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,since he found a clue to its location.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.72,0:03:52.34,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,We thought we'd invite your dad, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.35,0:03:54.67,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not going.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.91,0:03:59.15,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it's actually \NTokugawa's buried treasure,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.15,0:04:02.59,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,most of it will end up \Nbelonging to the state.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.90,0:04:05.65,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Guess you're not going, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.56,0:04:10.80,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Since we have a few days off, you \Nshould take this kid with you, Ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.80,0:04:14.49,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,But doesn't searching for \Nburied treasure sound scary?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.49,0:04:17.91,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,What? You should come with us, Ran-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.91,0:04:21.61,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,The mayor's covering all our travel expenses.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.61,0:04:25.14,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, if Heiji got a letter, as \Nthe other high school detective,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.14,0:04:29.97,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Kudo-kun might've received one, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.97,0:04:31.62,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sh-Shinichi got one?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.14,0:04:33.41,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.41,0:04:34.74,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.74,0:04:38.96,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Kudo said he was interested \Nin buried treasure before.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.40,0:04:40.88,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he'll be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.88,0:04:42.09,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, whoa, whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.09,0:04:44.58,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, so you should come with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.58,0:04:46.97,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think you're doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.14,0:04:48.65,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}It's not like I can't since we \Nhave a few days off, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.97,0:04:49.68,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You're not interested in \Nburied treasure either.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.68,0:04:51.21,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't have a choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.21,0:04:53.73,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,If she doesn't come, you can't come either.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.54,0:04:56.10,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You've got an ulterior motive, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.81,0:04:58.48,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.11,0:05:04.46,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, Tokugawa's buried treasure \Nis at Mt. Akagi in Gunma.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.46,0:05:08.37,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If there's another case, that \Nuseless inspector will show up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.06,0:05:10.64,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.64,0:05:13.62,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,We're not going to Gunma, \Nwe're going to Shizuoka.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.92,0:05:16.21,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Shizuoka?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.37,0:05:21.75,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for coming, Hattori Heiji-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.11,0:05:24.74,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,And your friends, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.74,0:05:27.63,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,I'm looking forward to unearthing \Nthis buried treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.93,0:05:32.01,Densuke,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Takekuma Densuke (58) \NYadori Village Mayor
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.15,0:05:32.01,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}After all, the fate of Yadori \NVillage depends on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.29,0:05:34.52,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But why did you write to Heiji-niichan?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.86,0:05:38.42,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There are other non-high \Nschool aged detectives.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.42,0:05:42.30,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, well, I also invited \Nhistorians and archaeologists,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.30,0:05:45.47,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,so the budget was tight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.17,0:05:48.92,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me, but I thought a high \Nschool detective would come
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.92,0:05:52.93,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,if I paid for his transportation and food.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.93,0:05:53.78,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.55,0:05:58.58,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,You'll pay for the bullet train \NI took to get here, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.92,0:06:00.89,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.83,0:06:08.34,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you must be joking!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.34,0:06:11.06,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,You really expect us to stay \Nin this run down hotel?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.29,0:06:16.23,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't look like much, but it's \Nsparkling clean on the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.68,0:06:19.33,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,I bought plenty of ingredients,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.33,0:06:22.02,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,so I'll do my best to \Nprepare a feast for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.02,0:06:23.77,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,You're cooking for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.10,0:06:29.03,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,There used to be droves of tourists \Nwho came to see Kurogane Lake.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.42,0:06:34.03,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,The hotel prospered, but \Nsince the incident...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.20,0:06:35.90,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What incident?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.90,0:06:36.93,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.93,0:06:39.08,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.31,0:06:42.33,DCMain,MICHIKI,0000,0000,0000,,A member of the team unearthing \NTokugawa's buried treasure
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.62,0:06:46.94,DCMain,MICHIKI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}died in an accident while excavating.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.92,0:06:48.55,Michiki,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Tanzawa Michiki (62) \NArchaeologist
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.53,0:06:48.56,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.56,0:06:52.85,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Do people really think there's \Nburied treasure around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.08,0:06:54.04,DCMain,MICHIKI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.04,0:06:57.91,DCMain,MICHIKI,0000,0000,0000,,Shizuoka is where Tokugawa Ieyasu retired,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.91,0:07:00.02,DCMain,MICHIKI,0000,0000,0000,,and Sunpu Castle once stood here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.39,0:07:03.73,DCMain,YASUKATSU,0000,0000,0000,,And there's a legend.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.48,0:07:09.27,DCMain,YASUKATSU,0000,0000,0000,,During the war, when Ieyasu was \Nnearly captured by Imagawa,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.27,0:07:13.24,DCMain,YASUKATSU,0000,0000,0000,,an old couple hid him \Nhere in Kurogane Forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.24,0:07:17.38,DCMain,YASUKATSU,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}After the country stabilized, he gave \Nthem a mountain of golden coins,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.49,0:07:18.45,Yasukatsu,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Someji Yasukatsu (55) \NHistorian
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.38,0:07:21.75,DCMain,YASUKATSU,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}to thank the couple and their \Nson for their kindness.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.04,0:07:23.07,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.07,0:07:24.33,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Is it true?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.33,0:07:27.80,DCMain,YASUKATSU,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. There's even a poem about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.80,0:07:29.30,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,"In the morning and evening sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.30,0:07:31.38,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,two thousand jars glitter
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.63,0:07:34.39,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,with a thousand golden coins."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.76,0:07:38.22,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,It's a nursery song that's been \Nsung in this town for ages.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.22,0:07:41.94,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,"In the morning and evening sun" \Nis a phrase that appears in poems
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.94,0:07:46.77,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,on the location of the buried \Ntreasure from throughout the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.02,0:07:53.21,Fumie,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Masuko Fumie (46) \NAuthor
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.04,0:07:51.68,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}But if there really are two thousand \Njars filled with a thousand gold coins,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.02,0:07:53.66,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}it would be truly romantic.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.04,0:07:56.82,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's two million gold coins.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.82,0:07:59.28,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,It would be so wonderful if it were true.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.28,0:08:00.47,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.01,0:08:04.44,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,You two cuties look like treasures
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.44,0:08:06.88,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,that glitter brighter than gold to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.88,0:08:08.05,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.23,0:08:09.52,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Who the hell are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.52,0:08:11.72,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, are they your girlfriends?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.03,0:08:14.62,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I asked you first!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.62,0:08:15.76,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Answer me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.17,0:08:20.72,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I'm a documentary writer who \Ntravels across the country
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.85,0:08:23.27,Hajime,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Tsurumi Hajime (22) \NDocumentary Writer
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.72,0:08:23.27,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}in search of local monster legends.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.48,0:08:23.99,DCItalic,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mon...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.99,0:08:24.69,DCItalic,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Monsters?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.24,0:08:28.27,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,What? That's got nothing \Nto do with buried treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.45,0:08:30.92,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,What? You haven't heard?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.60,0:08:33.36,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,This village actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.97,0:08:36.11,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, a dog!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.82,0:08:38.19,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,Stop that!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.19,0:08:39.79,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,I-I don't like dogs...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.04,0:08:41.19,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,He's cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.19,0:08:42.11,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.11,0:08:44.52,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,He was brought here by the member
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.52,0:08:47.04,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,of the excavation team \Nwho died in the accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.37,0:08:50.77,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,After the accident, the locals took him in,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.77,0:08:54.66,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,but since he kept escaping to come back here,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.66,0:08:56.55,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,we've let him be.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.04,0:09:01.72,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,The lake is just past the \Ntrees so it's a bit dangerous,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.72,0:09:04.56,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,but someone's been feeding him occasionally.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.56,0:09:08.44,Danger,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Stay Out \NDanger!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.41,0:09:08.44,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's a huge sign.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.07,0:09:12.86,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun, it's dangerous. \NYou can't go in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.71,0:09:18.48,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Is this everyone you invited here today?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.48,0:09:20.69,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Well, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.92,0:09:28.55,DCItalic,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Shinichi's not here, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.55,0:09:32.39,DCItalic,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I was planning to give him my answer \Nto what he said in London, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.14,0:09:37.61,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,What you said over the \Nphone had better be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.61,0:09:40.05,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,The view is magnificent.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.34,0:09:43.10,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Better than the view of \NBig Ben in the evening?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.10,0:09:46.58,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Of course. It doesn't even compare.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.58,0:09:48.38,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,You're sure, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.38,0:09:50.31,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,I guarantee it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.51,0:09:52.08,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Kazuha-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.08,0:09:55.10,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Did Hattori-kun invite you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.68,0:09:58.54,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. He asked if I was busy over the break.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.54,0:10:02.57,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,But now they're talking \Nabout cave-ins and monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.57,0:10:05.45,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,I have a bad feeling about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.45,0:10:07.46,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.90,0:10:09.86,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What you're feeling might be love.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.86,0:10:10.38,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.64,0:10:18.51,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm stuffed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.51,0:10:20.44,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't eat another bite.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.44,0:10:22.49,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,The stew was good.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.49,0:10:24.26,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Mister Mayor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.26,0:10:26.52,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,You're welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.94,0:10:29.32,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Now to finish it off,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.98,0:10:32.77,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,we put rice in the bowl
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.14,0:10:35.78,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,and cover it with beaten eggs.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.75,0:10:41.89,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Then you mix it with your chopsticks, \Nand the porridge is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.89,0:10:43.83,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What? You're mixing it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.83,0:10:47.26,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,But the eggs are fluffier if \Nyou just cover it instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.26,0:10:51.19,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,It all tastes like egg if you \Nmix it. It's delicious that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.74,0:10:56.93,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hear that monster story \Nyou started to tell us earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.93,0:10:58.92,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, that story?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.39,0:11:03.34,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,There was a foreigner named Charles \NAbel on the excavation team
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.34,0:11:06.06,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,who spoke broken Japanese.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.42,0:11:09.60,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,He's the one who got in the accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.60,0:11:13.23,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,When the rest of the team \Narrived, he was still alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.58,0:11:16.82,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,He was trying to say something \Nfrom under the rocks,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.82,0:11:19.57,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,so they asked him if he had found anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.57,0:11:23.24,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,But the foreigner's throat had been \Ndestroyed, and he couldn't speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.82,0:11:27.11,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,Someone on the team handed \Nhim a notebook and pen,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.11,0:11:30.63,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,and the foreigner slowly and \Ncarefully wrote three letters
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.63,0:11:33.50,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,from the alphabet on the page.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.90,0:11:38.51,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,The team members who saw the \Npage were frozen in fear
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.75,0:11:43.76,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,because that piece of paper had \Nthe word "nue" written on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.09,0:11:44.89,DCItalic,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Nue?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.89,0:11:45.76,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.98,0:11:48.42,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,N-Nue? You mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.42,0:11:51.06,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,That monster from folk tales?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.59,0:11:52.85,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.85,0:11:54.34,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,The head of a monkey,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.34,0:11:55.63,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,the body of a tanuki,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.63,0:11:57.11,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,the legs of a tiger,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.11,0:11:58.07,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,and the tail of a snake.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.65,0:12:02.34,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,It's an ancient monster that \Nappears in a cloud of black smoke
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.34,0:12:06.11,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,with an eerie cry to bring misfortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.85,0:12:10.01,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying one of those was in that cave?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.01,0:12:13.33,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I mean, what else could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.56,0:12:16.43,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I was invited here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.43,0:12:21.35,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,In order to tell the world about \Nthe monster that plunged
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.35,0:12:23.59,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,the excavation team into the depths of fear!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.14,0:12:28.51,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think you're doing, hag?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.73,0:12:32.02,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,Don't gleefully recount a person's death!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.02,0:12:35.14,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,Now you've ruined the porridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.75,0:12:40.95,DCMain,MICHIKI,0000,0000,0000,,I thought your novels covered similar themes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.39,0:12:43.03,DCMain,YASUKATSU,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.37,0:12:45.78,DCMain,YASUKATSU,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard to imagine those \Nwords coming from the woman
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.78,0:12:50.79,DCMain,YASUKATSU,0000,0000,0000,,who described in such grotesque detail \Nthe death of a man eaten by a monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.01,0:12:54.32,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, would it better if I left?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.32,0:12:56.79,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now, everyone. Let's try to get along.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.96,0:12:59.33,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we get a good night's sleep
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.33,0:13:02.46,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,and meet at the cave at the \Nexcavation site in the morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.63,0:13:09.33,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wh—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.68,0:13:12.82,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What is this weird sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.96,0:13:19.86,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,How unusual.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.12,0:13:21.36,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,Is it here?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.36,0:13:22.53,DCMain,YASUKATSU,0000,0000,0000,,In the forest?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.80,0:13:24.03,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"Is it here?"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.43,0:13:26.78,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,What is this sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.55,0:13:29.33,DCMain,MICHIKI,0000,0000,0000,,It's the cry...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.01,0:13:32.76,DCMain,MICHIKI,0000,0000,0000,,of the nue.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.27,0:13:41.92,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Th-The cry of the nue?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.14,0:13:44.93,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You mean it lives in this forest?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.93,0:13:48.43,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,That monster from folk tales?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.62,0:13:51.18,DCMain,MICHIKI,0000,0000,0000,,Not the monster, the bird.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.44,0:13:52.12,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.12,0:13:53.10,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,...a bird?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.34,0:13:58.50,DCMain,MICHIKI,0000,0000,0000,,It lives in hardwood forests in hilly areas.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.50,0:14:03.42,DCMain,MICHIKI,0000,0000,0000,,The scaly thrush was once called the nue.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.42,0:14:06.15,DCMain,MICHIKI,0000,0000,0000,,Since the cry of the monster that appeared
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.15,0:14:08.76,DCMain,MICHIKI,0000,0000,0000,,in the {\i1}Tale of Heike{\i0} sounded \Nsimilar to the bird's,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.76,0:14:11.41,DCMain,MICHIKI,0000,0000,0000,,it was called the nue.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.31,0:14:19.13,DCMain,MICHIKI,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't think the scaly thrush \Nlived around here, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.13,0:14:21.26,DCMain,MICHIKI,0000,0000,0000,,How unusual.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.26,0:14:26.09,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe the foreigner who died in the cave-in
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.09,0:14:28.17,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,saw the bird, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.52,0:14:30.74,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,All he wrote as he was dying
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.74,0:14:35.43,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,was "nue" in the English alphabet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.13,0:14:40.06,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.06,0:14:43.44,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,The foreigner saw it inside a \Ncave at the excavation site!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.62,0:14:45.32,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,It couldn't have been a bird!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.50,0:14:47.18,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,It really was there!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.18,0:14:51.82,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,Deep inside that cave, the legendary nue!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.23,0:14:54.71,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.71,0:14:57.68,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,but none of the surviving \Nmembers of the excavation team
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.68,0:15:00.43,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,saw the nue, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.43,0:15:03.34,DCMain,YASUKATSU,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, it may not be entirely false.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.66,0:15:08.47,DCMain,YASUKATSU,0000,0000,0000,,Long ago, the body of a nue fell on the \Nwestern side of Hamana Lake in Shizuoka.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.47,0:15:11.76,DCMain,YASUKATSU,0000,0000,0000,,The regions Nueshiro, Dosaki, \NHanebira, and Ona of Mikkabi
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.76,0:15:13.70,DCMain,YASUKATSU,0000,0000,0000,,in Hamamatsu City's North Ward
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.70,0:15:17.25,DCMain,YASUKATSU,0000,0000,0000,,are said to have gotten their names
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.25,0:15:21.06,DCMain,YASUKATSU,0000,0000,0000,,from the nue's head, body, wings,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.06,0:15:22.82,DCMain,YASUKATSU,0000,0000,0000,,and tail that fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.82,0:15:26.69,DCMain,YASUKATSU,0000,0000,0000,,It's even said that the nue's \Nlegs fell here in Yadori Village.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.18,0:15:32.20,DCMain,YASUKATSU,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Yadori Village was once written using \Nthe characters for "night" and "bird."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.74,0:15:37.45,Yadori,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(85,1)}Yadori (Night Bird)
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.20,0:15:35.84,DCMain,YASUKATSU,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Together they make the character for nue.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.20,0:15:37.45,Nue,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(85,1)}Nue
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.65,0:15:41.33,DCMain,YASUKATSU,0000,0000,0000,,So this sound could be not the bird, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.33,0:15:42.33,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.09,0:15:46.15,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.15,0:15:47.34,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,It stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.40,0:15:52.68,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, let's go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.98,0:15:55.68,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What? But we came all the way here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.68,0:16:01.75,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,And all those monster stories \Nwere heard second-hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.75,0:16:04.80,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,The foreigner writing the \Nword "nue" at his death
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.80,0:16:06.34,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,must be fake, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.34,0:16:09.24,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I actually have that piece of paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.24,0:16:10.69,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You do?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.97,0:16:17.58,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,See? It says "nue."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.90,0:16:22.97,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,After the cave-in, the previous \Nmayor found it next to the body
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.97,0:16:25.27,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,when they dug the foreigner out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.27,0:16:28.68,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,It's been kept at the town \Nhall for sixteen years.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.09,0:16:33.84,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Along with this old hairpin they \Nsupposedly found with the paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.20,0:16:35.34,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.01,0:16:41.04,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,If this dog belonged to that \Nforeigner, he must be pretty old.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.04,0:16:44.18,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,It wouldn't be strange if he \Ndropped dead any day now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.18,0:16:48.06,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,He was still a puppy when he had him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.30,0:16:51.73,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,What was found recently was \Nthis notebook with a page
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.73,0:16:54.58,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,that perfectly matches the \Ntorn edge of this piece of paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.58,0:16:56.87,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,It details where and how \Nthe team was excavating
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.87,0:17:02.08,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,the cave, and on the basis of what information.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.50,0:17:05.34,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,If we could go to the cave \Ntomorrow and describe
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.34,0:17:07.84,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,where the buried treasure might be found,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.84,0:17:10.95,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,while reading from this notebook
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.95,0:17:14.34,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,in front of a camera, you'd be \Ndoing Yadori Village a huge favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.67,0:17:18.11,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I see. He's making a video \Nto revitalize his town.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.11,0:17:22.85,DCItalic,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,So he never expected us to \Nfind any buried treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.96,0:17:29.11,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Rest well, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.47,0:17:34.11,DCMain,YASUKATSU,0000,0000,0000,,Did you get the beverage I requested?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.40,0:17:37.36,DCMain,YASUKATSU,0000,0000,0000,,I have trouble sleeping without it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.36,0:17:39.49,DCMain,MICHIKI,0000,0000,0000,,What about my sake?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.49,0:17:40.70,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,And mine?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.70,0:17:43.81,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I bought all of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.81,0:17:46.12,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,I'll bring them to your rooms later.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.88,0:17:49.38,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Someji-sama, you requested milk and whiskey.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.38,0:17:52.75,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Tanzawa-sama, you requested \NJapanese sake and dried cuttlefish.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.75,0:17:55.57,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Masuko-sama, you requested \Nwhite wine and soda water.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.57,0:17:59.14,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,And Tsurumi-sama, you requested \Ncola and potato chips, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.48,0:18:02.51,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I'll drink it from the \Nbottle, so I don't need a glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.69,0:18:04.24,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.24,0:18:07.34,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Hattori-sama, shall I bring \Nanything for your group?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.34,0:18:08.77,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Nah, we're fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.14,0:18:09.96,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.96,0:18:11.00,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.00,0:18:15.06,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,If we drink too many fluids, we'll have to \Nuse the bathroom in the middle of the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.06,0:18:18.78,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure if I'll be able to sleep tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.78,0:18:19.94,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.94,0:18:23.61,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,You should inspect your rooms \Nbefore you go to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.18,0:18:29.00,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,There was a desiccated mouse corpse \Nin the desk drawer of my room.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.00,0:18:30.17,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.37,0:18:34.34,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,That's odd. I thought I cleaned everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.83,0:18:39.43,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,If you're so scared, why don't \Nyou sleep with me in my room?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.86,0:18:43.78,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,You can sleep with the mice!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.78,0:18:45.47,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.58,0:18:57.79,DCMain,YASUKATSU,0000,0000,0000,,A letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.31,0:19:00.53,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.53,0:19:05.67,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to open the \Ndrawer, open it already.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.67,0:19:06.70,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.86,0:19:09.24,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,What if there's a mouse in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.72,0:19:11.46,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing like that in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.95,0:19:16.21,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's something inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.45,0:19:18.59,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like old notebooks.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.38,0:19:20.88,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder whose they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.88,0:19:22.51,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe someone forgot them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.85,0:19:28.54,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Th-That's terrifying.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.54,0:19:31.54,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,It's the same character \Nwritten over and over.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.54,0:19:33.83,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.83,0:19:38.23,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, the foreigner who died
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.23,0:19:40.28,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,was probably practicing his hiragana.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.28,0:19:40.78,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.78,0:19:45.53,Charles,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Charles Abel
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.14,0:19:45.53,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,See? It says Charles Abel on the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.75,0:19:50.86,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't that mean this is the room \Nthe dead foreigner stayed in?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.30,0:19:52.71,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,It's light outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.19,0:19:56.06,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.32,0:20:00.59,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,There's a fire in front of the hotel!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.59,0:20:01.34,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.67,0:20:02.30,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.72,0:20:04.92,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Run! There's a fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.81,0:20:09.56,Danger2,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Stay Out \NDanger!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.08,0:20:14.14,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Who could've done this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.91,0:20:22.16,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's the nue...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.00,0:20:26.16,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,The nue came in a cloud of black smoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.77,0:20:32.04,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,You idiot! There's no way \Nanything like that—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.04,0:20:33.94,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Heiji! Look...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.94,0:20:44.10,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's huge...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.10,0:20:45.51,DCItalic,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,What is this thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.54,0:20:57.01,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's leaving!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.65,0:20:58.72,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.72,0:21:00.90,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,We can't go after it this \Nway because of the fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.27,0:21:02.90,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Mayor, fire extinguishers!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.20,0:21:06.03,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Use all the fire extinguishers \Nhere to put out the fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.03,0:21:07.33,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,G-Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.33,0:21:09.90,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Kazuha, help them put out the fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.90,0:21:11.20,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.56,0:21:12.95,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't ask stupid questions!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.79,0:21:16.29,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going around back to find \Nout what that monster really is!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.29,0:21:17.29,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.39,0:21:27.36,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,There are huge teeth marks on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.36,0:21:28.43,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.88,0:21:30.26,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,That's weird, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.94,0:21:33.00,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,We ran around the back...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.36,0:21:36.10,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,...but we didn't pass the monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.47,0:21:39.76,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Could it have gone through the trees
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.76,0:21:42.28,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,and into the lake?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.33,0:21:48.40,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Blood?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.40,0:21:54.27,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It leads towards the lake.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.94,0:22:04.39,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,That's Someji-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.78,0:22:06.32,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Is he unconscious?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.67,0:22:09.12,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,No, he's already dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.70,0:22:15.56,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,With scratches on his back as though \Nhe was attacked by a wild beast.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.94,0:24:08.96,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.47,0:23:46.69,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,H-He's dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.88,0:23:48.34,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,It's the nue...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.34,0:23:51.07,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,That giant monster got him.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.40,0:23:53.29,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,It must've been some kind of trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.65,0:23:56.70,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I smell kerosene in these burns, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.96,0:23:58.21,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Where'd that fire come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.21,0:24:00.33,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know. It suddenly ignited.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.55,0:24:05.38,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What was that scream?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.96,0:24:14.97,DCNextEp,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Conan and Heiji's Nue \NLegend \N(Scratch Arc)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.62,0:24:14.56,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is "Conan and \NHeiji's Nue Legend, Scratch Arc!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.98,0:24:34.99,Hint,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Giant Monster
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.39,0:24:32.26,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.67,0:24:34.71,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A giant monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.99,0:24:36.12,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}My answer to London...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.99,0:24:39.99,Don'tMiss,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the next episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.12,0:24:37.20,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Am I feeling love?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.20,0:24:39.63,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}They're both acting weird...
